NemotronH speculative decoding (MTP) + radix (prefix) cache — upstream PR #27998.

Source: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/27998
  "[NemotronH] Enable speculative decoding (MTP) with radix cache" (Kh4L:sglang)
  Captured 2026-06-16 via `gh pr diff 27998` (4 commits, +~90 across 4 files).
  PR base merge-base: 2a51479a (main, 2026-06-11T05:14Z); PR head cc582d2b.
  PR state at capture: OPEN, CI red (both PR-test runs failing), NOT merged.
  REGENERATE from the merged commit once it lands, then DROP this patch when a
  release tag containing it is used (gate: recipe APPLY_NEMOTRONH_MTP_PR27998).

Why: NemotronH could previously only serve MTP with --disable-radix-cache,
  which re-prefills the (usually shared) context on every request. This makes
  MTP + radix (prefix) cache work together. Removes our "blocker 1" entirely
  (no --disable-radix-cache wiring needed in sglang_launch.sh). Validated by the
  PR author on GB10 (= DGX Spark) with nvidia/NVIDIA-Nemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B-
  NVFP4: 98% prefix reuse with MTP active, no decode/accuracy regression.
  See model_profiles/nvidia-nvidia-nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b-nvfp4.yml (MTP block).

What it does:
  - arg_groups/nemotron_h_hook.py: when spec + radix are both on and the mamba
    scheduler strategy is the default no_buffer, auto-switch it to extra_buffer
    (no_buffer raises in _handle_mamba_radix_cache; extra_buffer_lazy is not yet
    supported with speculative decoding). NB: this CONTRADICTS the old profile
    note "extra_buffer is rejected on NemotronH" — upstream now selects it here.
  - managers/schedule_batch.py: guard mamba_next_track_idx == None on the
    spec-v2 verify path (= #27324; drop that hunk if #27324 lands in the ref first).
  - mem_cache/memory_pool.py + model_executor/model_runner_kv_cache_mixin.py:
    log planned/per-request mamba allocation at startup (memory visibility on
    tight unified-memory boxes like GB10).

NOTE: captured against main merge-base 2a51479a but applied onto tag v0.5.13
  (the recipe's SGLANG_REF) — v0.5.13 has diverged from that merge-base
  (ahead 112 / behind 12). The four touched files are small + self-contained, so
  `patch` fuzz should absorb the drift; if the in-container dry-run FAILS, check
  out v0.5.13 and regenerate (apply the 4 PR commits / 3-way merge) before rebuild.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/arg_groups/nemotron_h_hook.py b/python/sglang/srt/arg_groups/nemotron_h_hook.py
index a4e17670f05a..f3a02b42bada 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/arg_groups/nemotron_h_hook.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/arg_groups/nemotron_h_hook.py
@@ -55,6 +55,23 @@ def apply_nemotron_h_defaults(server_args: "ServerArgs", model_arch: str) -> Non
         else:
             server_args.moe_runner_backend = "flashinfer_cutlass"

+    # NemotronH is MTP-centric. When speculative decoding and radix (prefix)
+    # cache are both enabled, the default no_buffer mamba scheduler strategy is
+    # incompatible (it raises in _handle_mamba_radix_cache), and
+    # extra_buffer_lazy is not yet supported with speculative decoding. Default
+    # to extra_buffer so MTP and prefix caching run together instead of forcing
+    # --disable-radix-cache (which re-prefills the shared context every request).
+    if (
+        server_args.speculative_algorithm is not None
+        and not server_args.disable_radix_cache
+        and server_args.mamba_scheduler_strategy == "no_buffer"
+    ):
+        server_args.mamba_scheduler_strategy = "extra_buffer"
+        logger.info(
+            f"Defaulting --mamba-scheduler-strategy to extra_buffer for {model_arch} "
+            "to enable speculative decoding (MTP) together with radix (prefix) cache."
+        )
+
     server_args._handle_mamba_radix_cache(
         model_arch=model_arch,
         sm100_default_attention_backend="flashinfer",
